23/06/2004
LISBON, Portugal -- Bulgaria ended its run in the 2004 European Championship, losing 2-1 to Italy on Tuesday (22 June). 
Martin Petrov scored his country's first goal in the tournament with a penalty kick in the last minute of the first half. 
The Italians came back with a goal by Simone Perrotta in the 48th minute. 
Antonio Cassano sealed the Italians' victory in the fourth minute of injury time. 
(AP, Reuters, AFP, Bloomberg, ESPN - 22/06/04)
